# CALIBRATION.md

## Purpose
Define quality bars, review expectations, and what “done” means for this repository.

This document aligns contributors on standards.

---

## Definition of done
A task is “done” when:
- Requirements are met
- Edge cases are considered
- Tests or validation are performed
- Documentation reflects reality

---

## Quality bar
- Code should be readable by someone new to the repo.
- Behavior should be predictable and testable.
- Cleverness is discouraged if it reduces clarity.

---

## Review expectations
Reviewers should check:
- Correctness
- Scope control
- Safety and edge cases
- Alignment with architecture and rules

---

## Risk posture
<Select one or describe>
- Risk-off / safety-first
- Balanced
- Move fast

---

## When to slow down
Explicitly slow down when:
- Money, safety, or data integrity is involved
- Making irreversible changes
- Touching core system boundaries
